    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 30th with **Yordan Alvarez** standing as our undisputed anchor. With a projection of 87.42, **Yordan Alvarez** leverages a massive +16% park factor and an elite BvP track record against Bassitt, making him the only player approaching our \"Elite\" tier today. Following him, **Colt Keith** (63.34) and **Kazuma Okamoto** (60.36) provide strong, reliable production against Elder and Ober respectively. While **Kazuma Okamoto** is pending official lineup confirmation in the #4 hole, his ability to capitalize on Ober\u2019s middling xERA makes him a high-floor start. Our strategy leans heavily into these matchups to compensate for a day where we must navigate a tough encounter with Logan Webb.\n\nThe primary conflict for today\u2019s lineup was between **Carson Benge** (56.03) and **Jerar Encarnacion** (39.39). While **Jerar Encarnacion** benefited from a platoon advantage against S\u00e1nchez, his low order position (#8) and the overall projection drag suppressed his score below our 40-point floor threshold. Consequently, **Jerar Encarnacion** occupies our top bench spot, as we prioritize **Carson Benge**\u2019s higher efficiency against Mikolas despite the park penalty. We remain cautious with **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber** facing Webb; while both provide decent value, the SP skill of Webb (-19%) and his elite catcher present significant risks to our SB and AVG categories. We are benching high-ceiling options like **Junior Caminero**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, **Christian Yelich**, **Caleb Durbin**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Chase Meidroth**, **Gary Sanchez**, **Luke Raley**, **Josh Smith**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Pedro Ramirez**, and **Luis Pena** today, mostly due to off-days, to ensure we keep our game caps optimized for high-value future starts.",
